                <note rend="inline" type="source">831.00/1–449: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Representatives in the American Republics,
                            Except Cuba and Venezuela</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-01-04">January 4,
                            1949</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Embassy Habana reports that prior to leaving Habana Jan 3 for visit in Miami
                    Gallegos told press he had received from State Dept completely satisfactory
                    explanation activities US in Caracas.</p>
                <p>Gallegos by this act has publicly confirmed what he stated privately some time
                    ago, namely his recognition that charges of US involvement in Venez coup are
                    completely false.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
